{"info": {"author": "Satheesh Kumar", "author_email": "satheesh.101097@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# iaBot\n\niaBot is a Python library for creating simple bots and serving it with the different ways available.\n\n\n[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/iaBot.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/iaBot) ![Build](https://github.com/satheesh1997/iaBot/workflows/Build%20&%20Publish/badge.svg)\n\n\n\n\n## Installation\n\nUse the package manager [pip](https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/) to install iaBot.\n\n```bash\npip install iaBot\n```\n\n## A simple bot\n\n```python\nfrom iabot import CreateBot\nfrom iabot.handlers import SystemInformationHandler\nfrom iabot.servers import HttpServer\n\nhandlers = [\n   SystemInformationHandler\n]\nbot = CreateBot(\n   handlers=handlers\n)\nbot_server = HttpServer(bot)\nbot_server.run()\n```\n\nThis creates a simple bot that will be listening to HttpRequests on the port 8000. Using any tool available send a post request to http://<your_domain.com>:8000/ with the following data.\n```json\n{\n  \"handler\": \"system\",\n  \"action\": \"time\"\n}\n\n```\nOn successfull request you will get time in the response as json.\n\n### Handlers\nThese are used to group a set of similar actions. You can create your own handlers by inheriting the base handler.\n```python\nfrom iabot.handlers import BaseHandler\n\nclass StockHandler(BaseHandler):\n    handle = 'stock'\n\n    def get_stocks(self, *args, **kwargs):\n      .....\n      ....\n\n```\n\nOnce you create a handler with the actions you can register it to a bot by adding the handler to the list of handlers.\n\n### Actions\nThese are functions that a bot can execute to do the job when asked for. In the above StockHandler, get_stocks is an action. The response of all the actions should be a dictionary.\n\nWhen a request reaches the server it will execute the particular action inside the handler. You can also send some additional data to your actions by passing it as a dict using data key in the request data. Remember a handler should always return a dict.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"handler\": \"stock\",\n  \"action\": \"get_stocks\",\n  \"data\": {\n     \"date\": \"04-5-2010\"\n   }\n}\n\n```\n\nWill be updating more and adding more type of servers to serve the bot.\n\n## Contributing\nPull requests are welcome. For major changes, please open an issue first to discuss what you would like to change.\n\nPlease make sure to update tests as appropriate.\n\n\n## -\n![Python Powered](https://www.python.org/static/community_logos/python-powered-h-70x91.png)\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/satheesh1997/iaBot", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "iaBot", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/iaBot/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/iaBot/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/satheesh1997/iaBot"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/iaBot/0.0.7/", "requires_dist": ["Flask (==1.1.2)", "pytest (==5.3.2)", "websockets (==8.1)"], "requires_python": ">=3.7.0", "summary": "A mini framework for building bots using python and can be served using different ways.", "version": "0.0.7", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>iaBot</h1>\n<p>iaBot is a Python library for creating simple bots and serving it with the different ways available.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://badge.fury.io/py/iaBot\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"PyPI version\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/7d0738e5c45364bb0ad3d4882ef04113189edf11/68747470733a2f2f62616467652e667572792e696f2f70792f6961426f742e737667\"></a> <img alt=\"Build\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/146b1b270f968e6e55d92bad0cd5cd34658b9491/68747470733a2f2f6769746875622e636f6d2f7361746865657368313939372f6961426f742f776f726b666c6f77732f4275696c64253230262532305075626c6973682f62616467652e737667\"></p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Use the package manager <a href=\"https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/\" rel=\"nofollow\">pip</a> to install iaBot.</p>\n<pre>pip install iaBot\n</pre>\n<h2>A simple bot</h2>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">iabot</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">CreateBot</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">iabot.handlers</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">SystemInformationHandler</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">iabot.servers</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">HttpServer</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">handlers</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span>\n   <span class=\"n\">SystemInformationHandler</span>\n<span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">bot</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">CreateBot</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n   <span class=\"n\">handlers</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">handlers</span>\n<span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">bot_server</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">HttpServer</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">bot</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">bot_server</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">run</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</pre>\n<p>This creates a simple bot that will be listening to HttpRequests on the port 8000. Using any tool available send a post request to http://&lt;your_domain.com&gt;:8000/ with the following data.</p>\n<pre><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"nt\">\"handler\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"system\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"nt\">\"action\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"time\"</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</pre>\n<p>On successfull request you will get time in the response as json.</p>\n<h3>Handlers</h3>\n<p>These are used to group a set of similar actions. You can create your own handlers by inheriting the base handler.</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">iabot.handlers</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">BaseHandler</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">class</span> <span class=\"nc\">StockHandler</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">BaseHandler</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">handle</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s1\">'stock'</span>\n\n    <span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">get_stocks</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">args</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"o\">**</span><span class=\"n\">kwargs</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n      <span class=\"o\">.....</span>\n      <span class=\"o\">....</span>\n</pre>\n<p>Once you create a handler with the actions you can register it to a bot by adding the handler to the list of handlers.</p>\n<h3>Actions</h3>\n<p>These are functions that a bot can execute to do the job when asked for. In the above StockHandler, get_stocks is an action. The response of all the actions should be a dictionary.</p>\n<p>When a request reaches the server it will execute the particular action inside the handler. You can also send some additional data to your actions by passing it as a dict using data key in the request data. Remember a handler should always return a dict.</p>\n<pre><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"nt\">\"handler\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"stock\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"nt\">\"action\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"get_stocks\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"nt\">\"data\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n     <span class=\"nt\">\"date\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"04-5-2010\"</span>\n   <span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</pre>\n<p>Will be updating more and adding more type of servers to serve the bot.</p>\n<h2>Contributing</h2>\n<p>Pull requests are welcome. For major changes, please open an issue first to discuss what you would like to change.</p>\n<p>Please make sure to update tests as appropriate.</p>\n<h2>-</h2>\n<p><img alt=\"Python Powered\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/2dc22b6f963a79aac67ce24bfd2528c25d7cdd7b/68747470733a2f2f7777772e707974686f6e2e6f72672f7374617469632f636f6d6d756e6974795f6c6f676f732f707974686f6e2d706f77657265642d682d37307839312e706e67\"></p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7082549, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "a18b79578300438307508339194da588", "sha256": "ebeaf4b296345c19c8770f6a8c3560e695ecd8d7dd9254819fc0597de6b2dd4c"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "iaBot-0.0.1-py3.7.egg", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "a18b79578300438307508339194da588", "packagetype": "bdist_egg", "python_version": "3.7", "requires_python": ">=3.7.0", "size": 6807, "upload_time": "2020-04-16T12:39:38", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-16T12:39:38.474543Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/e9/6c/9acddc01580575d811620ada4a51ee7dd4a1e8e58c541db02e5290cbac81/iaBot-0.0.1-py3.7.egg", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "2918fa676f22a1d27c30760269eb71ad", "sha256": "ce77adfccd487c2552a5b6fc177fd67d2420ef1f64bbb761b62de689ee58bc7b"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "iaBot-0.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "2918fa676f22a1d27c30760269eb71ad", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.7.0", "size": 4171, "upload_time": "2020-04-16T12:39:35", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020